{
  "stem": "27285.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That it was impossible to take children on a journey like this.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we stayed behind.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Meanwhile, unfortunately, Hitler came to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so we were thrown out of this children's home.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were 30 children-- I only can tell you now, from this 30 children, only three survived, and without their brothers or sisters.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So it's only Jackie, Alex, and me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So that's probably the percentage, anyway, of all these happenings then.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know, but only-- I know it was immediately closed the moment the Germans came, or after a month or two, and we were thrown into a Jewish orphanage.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this was quite horrid because, first of all, the orphans knew that we are children with parents, so that's already nothing in common.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then we did not have the language, we did not speak Czech, of course, we spoke German.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So this was also not very agreeable.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was quite a hard time to overcome these obstacles.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were thrown also out of the school, and so-- anyway, one way to learn another language, that's-- I acquired the Czech language, which I spoke until '46.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I did not utter a word in German.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Of course, I am fluent in German, because I was always read it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my first-- talking German again was when I came to Palestine because my parents, unfortunately, did not have any other language.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So when I finally met them-- and I did, which was lucky, I had to speak German, again.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not an outsider, because these were my enemies, so, I was not against the language.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But also in Terezin I was only with Czech children, so I spoke Czech, and I read Czech, and we played Czech, and that's it.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
